  # Real-World Grounding Layer Plan

  ## Summary

  Add a shared egress_grounding package that converts local public/deidentified datasets into privacy-safe normalized JSONL grounding records, then lets both
  existing generators optionally use those records while still rendering through local templates. Default generator behavior remains synthetic-only, so
  existing commands and tests keep working without grounding files.

  The implementation will not copy raw CFPB narratives, Banking77 utterances, PubMed abstracts, NHANES participant rows, or Berka identifiers into generated
  examples. Grounded outputs will remain synthetic, with provenance stored only under meta.grounding.

  ## Key Changes

  - Add src/egress_grounding/ with:
      - schemas.py: GroundingRecord, validation enums, JSONL serialization.
      - store.py: GroundingStore loading/indexing/sampling by domain, label, subtype, role, dataset.
      - registry.py: adapter registry for cfpb, banking77, berka, nhanes, pubmed, generic_jsonl.
      - sanitization.py: hashed IDs, unsafe identifier checks, numeric rounding/perturbation helpers.
      - overlap.py: English token-span and CJK character-span source-copy detection.
      - cli_prepare.py: offline conversion CLI with --dataset, --input, --output, --seed, --limit.
      - cli_validate.py: schema/safety/coverage validation CLI with non-zero exit on invalid files.

  - Add adapters:
      - CFPB CSV: categorical scenario/style features only, hashed complaint IDs, no raw narrative retention.
      - Banking77 CSV/JSON/JSONL: intent mapping to private candidates or public financial hard negatives, no utterance copying.
      - Berka directory: aggregate distribution records from .asc files, no raw account/client/transaction/loan IDs.
      - NHANES CSV/XPT: alias-based variable extraction, plausible clinical filtering, hashed/discarded SEQN, safe rounded fact bundles.
      - PubMed XML/JSONL: streaming XML parsing into public health hard-negative topics.
      - Generic JSONL: strict validation of already-normalized fact bundles.

  - Add data/grounding/README.md, data/grounding/raw/.gitkeep, data/grounding/processed/.gitkeep, and .gitignore rules that ignore real raw/processed
    grounding files while preserving docs/placeholders.

  ## Generator Integration

  - Extend SyntheticFinancialGenerator and SyntheticHealthGenerator constructors with:
      - grounding_store: GroundingStore | None = None
      - grounding_mode: str = "synthetic-only"
      - grounding_ratio: float = 0.0
      - optional dataset filter support

  - Modes:
      - synthetic-only: current behavior, unchanged default.
      - hybrid: use compatible grounding records for about grounding_ratio of eligible private and hard-negative rows; fall back to existing catalog
        generation and report fallback counts.

      - grounded-only: require compatible grounding coverage; fail with a coverage report if no safe compatible record exists for requested generation paths.

  - Grounded rows still use existing templates, formats, styles, and validators. Grounding facts only override compatible context fields.
  - Grounded private rows use source="grounded_synthetic".
  - Grounded public hard negatives use source="grounded_public_negative".
  - Mixed-egress rows inherit the embedded private payload’s meta.grounding.
  - Add repeatable CLI options to both generation CLIs:
      - --grounding PATH
      - --grounding-mode synthetic-only|hybrid|grounded-only
      - --grounding-ratio FLOAT
      - --grounding-dataset DATASET

  - Extend manifests with an optional grounding section containing mode, requested/actual ratio, datasets, grounded counts, fallback counts, source-role
    counts, raw_text_copied=false, and grounded_in_public_or_deidentified_data=true.

  - Preserve contains_real_personal_data=false.

  ## Splitting And Safety

  - Replace current split grouping key with a grounding-aware key:
      - grounded rows: grounding:{dataset}:{source_group_id}
      - non-grounded rows: existing meta.skeleton_id fallback behavior

  - Keep all variants from the same grounded source group in one split.
  - Keep current financial and health filters intact; add shared grounding validation before generation.
  - For narrative adapters, run overlap checks against temporary source text and reject generated/normalized content that contains suspicious long spans.
  - For NHANES and Berka, use rounded, bucketed, sampled, or slightly perturbed values; never reproduce complete source rows.

  ## Tests

  Add artificial fixtures under tests/fixtures/ only. No real dataset extracts.

  Required test coverage:

  - Adapter mapping and safety tests for CFPB, Banking77, Berka, NHANES, PubMed, and generic JSONL.
  - CLI tests for prepare/validate, valid and invalid grounding records, manifests, multiple --grounding inputs.
  - Generator tests for:
      - unchanged synthetic-only behavior
      - financial and health hybrid grounded metadata
      - grounded-only insufficient coverage failure
      - deterministic output for fixed seed
      - mixed-egress grounding inheritance
      - source-group-isolated train/validation split
      - existing centroid and dataset-quality tooling accepting grounded rows

  - Run the full suite with:
      - uv run python -m pytest

  ## Documentation

  Create README_grounding.md covering architecture, local dataset acquisition, input formats, preparation, validation, generation, privacy transformations,
  source-group splitting, generic JSONL use, licensing/access notes, and limitations.

  Update README.md and README_health.md with the full workflow:

  Acquire dataset manually
  → place under data/grounding/raw
  → prepare normalized grounding JSONL
  → validate grounding records
  → generate hybrid anchors and mixed egress
  → run dataset quality checks
  → build centroids
  → evaluate on source-group-isolated validation data

  Include commands for:

  - CFPB, Banking77, Berka, NHANES, PubMed preparation.
  - Financial grounded generation.
  - Health grounded generation.
  - Validation and quality checking.

  ## Assumptions And Defaults

  - No automatic downloads and no network use in tests.
  - pandas is optional: required only for NHANES XPT; CSV NHANES fixtures work without it.
  - --grounding-dataset filters loaded normalized records by dataset name; if omitted, all loaded records are eligible.
  - Multiple generated variants may use the same grounding source group, but splitting keeps that group isolated.
  - Existing benchmark, centroid, augmentation, and quality-check behavior is preserved except that they accept new source values and optional
    meta.grounding.

  - Current uncommitted benchmark-related work is left untouched unless a grounding change must interact with it.
